            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2415Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pan and <strong>juices</strong> to a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>spice paste</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>browned chicken</strong>, <strong>halved</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> and <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until thickened to a curry-like consistency and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Keralan-style chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2415Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2415Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2415Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
